Rancher is a GUI tool to mamage K8S cluster íntead of using CLI (command line interface) to manage
Thus Rancher is intuitive to use as an optional GUI tool to manage your cluster
Rancher can be íntalled directly on cluster

For detail information, see https://www.rancher.com/quick-start

# key things you need to know

- how to download KubeConfig and store it in your local ~/.kube/config file
- select correct namespace you want to work

